commit.message: Bump version to 0.12.3

Fix timeout handling for expected failures. (#26)

Normally, core Tasty provides timeout handling, but this is outside of
the local expected-failure wrapper, so a timeout shows up as an actual
failure, even if wrapped in an expected-failure wrapper.

This change gets the timeout value from the original test to apply
internally, and sets the Tasty timeout option for the test to
NoTimeout so that only local timeout management is occurring.

commit.message:
Enhance to show both exceptions and timeouts as expected failures.

Previously exceptions and timeouts were not caught, so an `expectFail`
could not capture these situations and report them as expected
failures.

This change provides internal exception catching and (duplication of)
timing to allow `expectFail` to be used for those failures as well.

The ability to catch timeouts requires an unfortunate hack of slightly
shortening the timeout period, so that the wrapped timeout in
`expectFail` fires before the outer timeout in Tasty itself.  This is
an unfortunate kludge, but given the overall sequencing of Tasty and
the dis-inclination of the Tasty developers to integrate this package
into the core Tasty functionality, it's pretty much unavoidable.

Fixes Issue #6
